race.comment: DOTHRAKI (6) has been superb since arriving at Esperance and he can continue that form here. Out to the mile now, but that shouldn't be an issue having won twice at this trip previously. The stable's strike jockey hops on board, he has the speed to roll across and he can repeat the dose. TRUE CHANCE (8) showed glimpses fresh before jumping an odds-on pop last start and missing by 0.8L when left with too much to do. Fitter again now with Faithfull hopping on board. Likely to get back in the run again, but loves this track and trip and can go one better. TACITO (4) disappointed last start but looks nicely placed here out to the mile for the first time. He maps to get a lovely run in transit and he can make his presence felt. MIDNIGHT RUSH (11) is right up in trip now, but is a winner over the mile previously. Too good last start and rates highly on that effort. THE JESTER'S SON (5) can improve on the plain fresh effort.
